headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 32 points, Jaren Jackson Jr. added 31 points and 10 rebounds and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Orlando Magic 123-115 on Thursday night for their fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant, Jackson lead Grizzlies over Magic for 5th straight

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum and the Celtics answered a head-scratching loss with the Boston star's second career triple-double in a blowout of Luka Doncic and the Mavericks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum's rare triple-double leads Celtics past Mavs, 124-95

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen scored a career-high 49 points to lead the Utah Jazz to a 131-114 victory over the Houston Rockets on Thursday night that snapped a five-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen has career-best 49 as Jazz down Rockets 131-114

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray sparked Denver early by scoring 13 of his 18 points in the first quarter, and the Nuggets led by as many as 43 in cruising to a 122-91 win over the Los Angeles Clippers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray's early exploits lead Nuggets to rout of Clippers
